{"questionId":"26494","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A company produces bags of sugar with a labelled weight of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>kg</mtext></math>. The weights of the bags are&nbsp;normally distributed with a mean of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>kg</mtext></math> and a standard deviation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math>. In an inspection, if&nbsp;the weight of a randomly chosen bag is less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>950</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math> then the company fails the inspection.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that the company fails the inspection.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> be the weight of sugar in the bag</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>950</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>308537</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>≈</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>309</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26494","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the probability that the company fails the inspection.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}